				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^2$$\end{document}S1/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_{1/2}$$\end{document} electronic level [218]. Cesium was chosen as it possesses only one natural isotope, so that no reduction of signal-to-noise ratio occurs as would be the case if different underlying hyperfine-structure splittings were present. The accuracy of the Cs-clock was further improved in the following decades. Important use was made of laser cooling, leading to the development of the Cs-fountain clocks in the early 1990s [72] that achieved inaccuracies in the 10-16\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
