				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^3$$\end{document} or more in this way. The same effect was later also discussed by Typel and Leclercq-Willain [386] and reviewed in [216]. A recent publication considering the same process for thorium ions under the name “laser-induced electronic bridge” (LIEB) is found in [27] (see also [28]). The process has not yet been experimentally observed.

