Two different EB excitation mechanisms were distinguished [355]: an elastic EB, in which the final electronic level equals the initial one, and an inelastic EB, where the electronic levels of the initial and the final states differ. For 229m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
