				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^{229\text {m}}$$\end{document}Th, the inelastic EB process was found to be more efficient, as it allows for shell excitation with an E1 transition and a decay via an M1 transition, which most efficiently excites the nucleus.

